In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. In order to assess relative binding affinities of the test compounds for aggregated Î±-synuclein, competition assays were set up with a radiolabeled molecule already known to bind to Î±-synuclein fibrils and non-radiolabeled test compounds. In order to induce its aggregation, Î±-synuclein was incubated in phosphate buffered saline (PBS, pH 7.4) at 37Â° C. for three days with shaking (1,400 rpm). Competitive binding assays were carried out in 12Ã75 mm borosilicate glass tubes. The reaction mixture contained 100 Î¼L of Î±-synuclein aggregates (0.5-1 Î¼g), [3H] positive reference compound #1 (100-200 nM diluted in PBS) and 50 Î¼L of competing compounds (10â?-10â? In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

Competitive Binding Assay: The compounds prepared in the preceding examples were found to bind with high affinity to Î±-synuclein aggregates/fibrils that are found in the hallmark Lewy Bodies of Parkinson's disease. In order to assess relative binding affinities of the test compounds for aggregated Î±-synuclein, competition assays were set up with a radiolabeled molecule already known to bind to Î±-synuclein fibrils and non-radiolabeled test compounds. In order to induce its aggregation, Î±-synuclein was incubated in phosphate buffered saline (PBS, pH 7.4) at 37Â° C. for three days with shaking (1,400 rpm). Competitive binding assays were carried out in 12Ã75 mm borosilicate glass tubes. The reaction mixture contained 100 Î¼L of Î±-synuclein aggregates (0.5-1 Î¼g), [3H] positive reference compound #1 (100-200 nM diluted in PBS) and 50 Î¼L of competing compounds (10â?-10â? M, diluted serially in PBS containing 0.1% bovine serum albumin) in a final volume of 0.25 ml.

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.

Inhibition of alpha-synuclein (unknown origin) self-aggregation by fluorescence polarization assay

In Vitro Inhibition Assay: Î±-Synucleinopathies are characterised by aggregation of Î±-synuclein in neurons. Aggregation of purified Î±-synuclein is performed essentially as described by Gerard et al. FASEB. 20(3):524-6 (2006). 20-100 Î¼g purified Î±-synuclein (Sigma; S7820) at a concentration of about 2.5 Î¼g/mL is incubated in the presence of spermin (250 Î¼M) or paraquat (32 mM) or 6-hydroxydopamine (400 Î¼M) or vehicle in a 384 well plate. Spermin, paraquat and 6-hydroxydopamine promote the Î±-synuclein aggregation process. Aggregation kinetics is determined by measuring turbidity at 340 nm, every 1-15 minutes for at least one hour.
